OL,4,CWomen detainees on period 'ignored'
OL,5,  Police are "routinely ignoring" the
OL,6, needs of women detainees on their
OL,7, periods, the Independent Custody
OL,8, Visiting Association (ICVA) has said.
OL,10,FThe way menstruating suspects are being
OL,11,Ftreated in police detention could be in
OL,12,Fbreach of human rights and equality
OL,13,Flaws, according to the IVCA, which
OL,14,Fmonitors the treatment of detainees.
OL,16,FIt called on the home secretary to
OL,17,Fintroduce new guidelines for police.
OL,19,FThe Home Office said everyone held in
OL,20,Fcustody should be treated with dignity.
